-comments
  Comments start with a #, and Python will render the rest of the line as a comment.

-Python Indentation
  Indentation refers to the spaces at the beginning of a code line.
  Where in other programming languages the indentation in code is for readability only, the indentation in Python is very important.
  Python uses indentation to indicate a block of code.


- To install Python on your Windows, just follow these steps:
  Install VS Code-- VS code is a different, much larger program (full IDE) also made by Microsoft, mainly used for C#/.NET development
  Download Python Installer File-- from the python officals
  Run the Installer-- check the environments
  Install Python
  Verify your installation-- using command python --version
